commit.message:
Allow context switch in test to ease stopping it.

Makes tests pass on Python 3.9 on Windows. #3629
Timeout to Libdoc tests to avoid hanging
UG: Fix kwargs example. Fixes #3621.

Tidy: Don't add extra spaces to doc lines containing just '...'.

Fixes #3618.
Remove not used test file

Update Pillow used by atests to more secure one.

Problem reported by dependabot. It doesn't really affect us, though.

Update info related to Python version support.

- Official Python 3.9 support in setup.py (#3629).

- Update info related to which Python versions which RF versions
  support in installation instructions.

Consistent line number with decorated libraries.

Otherwise Python 3.9 and newer return the line number of the first
decorator and older return line number of the actual class
statement. Now we use the latter semantics regardless the Python
version.

Also add test to get line number of a class based library created
without using the `class` statement.

Fixes #3628.

Avoid ElementTree API removed in Python 3.9.

Fixes #3627.

Screenshot: Fix using new scrot versions when overwriting screenshot.

Fixes #3636.

Allow running with any Python 3 interpreter.

No need to require Python 3.6 to be installed.
Python 3.5 doesn't work, though.

Ignore venv dirs with optional post-fix.

Allows creating venvs for different interpreters like venv27 and venv39.
Update rf-3.2.1.rst
